<concept id="concept_CB06FE80465A4C55866FC9DCC1A7B640"> 
  <title>Getting Started</title> 
  <shortdesc>Steps to take to start using the Adobe Marketing Cloud. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <conbody> 
	 <table id="table_DF3A0DFCA34C4A40BD7930E07FB28C00"> 
		<tgroup cols="2"> 
		  <colspec colname="col01" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*"/> 
		  <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="3.68*"/> 
		  <thead> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">Task 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2">Description 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
		  </thead> 
		  <tbody> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01"> 
				  <p><image href="graphics/step1_icon.png"
					 id="image_2FE443C494F14522ADCBFB805A2D043B"></image> 
					 <xref
					  href="access.xml#concept_04341546E8B44CDF833F9DDF351A50B9" format="dita"
					  scope="local">Get access</xref> 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2"> 
				  <p><b> Important:</b> Before you can sign in, your administrator
					 must contact Adobe for company provisioning. Administrators also need to create
					 groups and add users. 
				  </p> 
				  <p>See 
					 <xref
					  href="admin_getting_started.xml#concept_A9A190B372C5450CA53D60431D362143"
					  format="dita" scope="local">Administration - Getting Started</xref> for
					 instructions. 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01"> 
				  <p><image href="graphics/step2_icon.png"
					 id="image_4BA3A478FE684905AFA761521272C57A"></image> 
					 <xref
					  href="collaborate.xml#concept_5200BB842976461397C091178ED57756" format="dita"
					  scope="local">Collaborate</xref> 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2"> 
				  <p>Bring team members together through the common working
					 environment in Adobe Marketing Cloud. Each contributor is able to share
					 reports, content, assets, and feedback in real time. 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01"> 
				  <p><image href="graphics/step3_icon.png"
					 id="image_94FBBB77C1CB45F9B4F12E0C4D45B4CE"></image> Leverage core services
					 like 
					 <xref
					  href="audience_library.xml#concept_3D52E1DED6D04ECC949B514E182C4655"
					  format="dita" scope="local">Audiences</xref>. 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2"> 
				  <p>Core services like Audiences integrate with Marketing Cloud
					 solutions. For example, you can create audiences, combine existing audiences to
					 create composite audiences, and view all shared audiences. 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
		  </tbody> 
		</tgroup> 
	 </table> 
  </conbody>
</concept>
